      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ISLA ROCHELLE (9) is racing in fine form, adding to a string of wins and placings at this circuit and distance when scoring by close to 7m last week. Comes from the outside barrier this time but had a similar draw when she won earlier in the month. Going well enough to overcome that barrier and win again. JILLIBY ILLUMINATE NZ (7) looks close to a win after finishing runner-up in her two starts here since switching from Victoria. Raced parked and boxed on behind ISLA ROCHELLE last week. Draws inside that rival and is a chance to turn the tables. ALFNALMA (8) is a capable mare who returned to winning form at Bathurst last time, working forward from a similar barrier to lead before beating the boys by 1.6m. Can measure up. SUNSET STRIDE (6) should be nearing peak fitness fourth up. Exotic player.",
